Name: Sweepy
Description:
An automated sweeping robot.

Sweeps up Solid debris and Liquid spills and stores the material back in its Sweepy Dock.

Name: Coral Bug
Description:
Shine Bugs emit a soft Light in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Coral morph has been turned pink through selective breeding.

Name: Royal Bug
Description:
Shine Bugs emit a soft Light in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Royal morph has been turned purple through selective breeding.

Name: Shove Vole
Description:
Shove Voles are burrowing critters that eat the Regolith collected on terrestrial surfaces.

They cannot burrow through Refined Metals.

Name: Delecta Vole
Description:
Delecta Voles are burrowing critters whose bodies sprout shearable Tonic Root when Regolith is ingested at preferred temperatures.

They cannot burrow through Refined Metals.

Name: Gassy Moo
Description: Moos are extraterrestrial critters that feed on Gas Grass and excrete Natural Gas.

Name: Slickster
Description: Slicksters are slimy critters that consume Carbon Dioxide and exude Crude Oil.

Name: Longhair Slickster
Description:
Longhair Slicksters are friendly critters that consume Oxygen and thrive in close contact with Duplicant companions.

Longhairs have extremely beautiful and luxurious coats.

Name: Molten Slickster
Description: Molten Slicksters are slimy critters that consume Carbon Dioxide and exude Petroleum.

Name: Puft Prince
Description: The Puft Prince is a lazy critter that excretes little Solid lumps of whatever it has been breathing.

Name: Squeaky Puft
Description: Squeaky Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete lumps of Bleachstone with each breath.

Name: Puft
Description: Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete lumps of Slime with each breath.

Name: Dense Puft
Description: Dense Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete condensed Oxylite with each breath.

Name: Rover
Description: A curious bot that can remotely explore new Planetoid locations.

Name: Pip
Description:
Pips are pesky, nonhostile critters that subsist on Thimble Reeds and Arbor Tree branches.

They are known to bury Seeds in the ground whenever they can find a suitable area with enough space.

Name: Cuddle Pip
Description:
Cuddle Pips are fluffy, affectionate critters who exhibit a strong snuggling instinct towards all types of eggs.

This is temporarily amplified when they are hugged by a passing Duplicant.

Name: Sun Bug
Description:
Shine Bugs emit a soft Light in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Sun morph has been turned orange through selective breeding.

Name: Radiant Bug
Description:
Shine Bugs emit a soft Light in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Radiant morph has been amplified through selective breeding.

Name: Beeta Hive
Description:
A moderately Radioactive nest made by Beetas.

Converts Uranium into Enriched Uranium when worked by a Beeta.
Will not function if ground below has been destroyed.

Name: Beeta
Description:
Beetas are hostile critters that thrive in Radioactive environments.

They commonly gather Uranium for their Beeta Hives to produce Enriched Uranium.

Name: Pokeshell
Description:
Pokeshells are nonhostile critters that eat Polluted Dirt and Rot Piles.

The shells they leave behind after molting can be crushed into Lime.

Name: Sanishell
Description:
Sanishells are nonhostile critters that thrive in  Water and eliminates Germs from any liquid it inhabits.

They eat Polluted Dirt, Slime and Rot Piles.

Name: Oakshelll
Description:
Oakshells are nonhostile critters that eat Polluted Dirt, Slime and Rot Piles.

The shells they leave behind after molting can be crushed into Lumber.

Oakshells thrive in Ethanol.

Name: Sweetle
Description:
Sweetles are nonhostile critters that excrete large amounts of solid Sucrose.

They are closely related to the Grubgrub and exhibit similar, albeit less effective farming behaviors.

Name: Grubgrub
Description:
Grubgrubs form symbiotic relationships with plants, especially Grubfruit Plants, and instinctually tend to them.

Grubgrubs are closely related to Sweetles.

Name: Drecko
Description:
Dreckos are nonhostile critters that graze on Pincha Pepperplants, Balm Lily or Mealwood Plants.

Their backsides are covered in thick woolly fibers that only grow in Hydrogen climates.

Name: Glossy Drecko
Description:
Glossy Dreckos are nonhostile critters that graze on live Mealwood Plants and Bristle Blossoms.

Their backsides are covered in bioplastic scales that only grow in Hydrogen climates.

Name: Morb
Description: Morbs are attracted to unhygienic conditions and frequently excrete bursts of Polluted Oxygen.

Name: Hatch
Description: Hatches excrete solid Coal as waste and may be uncovered by digging up Buried Objects.

Name: Stone Hatch
Description: Stone Hatches excrete solid Coal as waste and enjoy burrowing into the ground.

Name: Smooth Hatch
Description: Smooth Hatches enjoy burrowing into the ground and excrete Refined Metal when fed Metal Ore.

Name: Sage Hatch
Description: Sage Hatches excrete solid Coal as waste and enjoy burrowing into the ground.

Name: Abyss Bug
Description: This Shine Bug emits no Light, but it makes up for it by having an excellent personality.

Name: Azure Bug
Description:
Shine Bugs emit a soft Light in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Azure morph has been turned blue through selective breeding.

Name: Shine Bug
Description: Shine Bugs emit a soft Light in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

Name: Plug Slug
Description:
Plug Slugs are dynamic creatures that generate electrical Power during the night.

Their power can be harnessed by leaving an exposed wire near areas where they like to sleep.

Name: Gulp Fish
Description: Every organism in the known universe finds the Pacu extremely delicious.

Name: Tropical Pacu
Description: Every organism in the known universe finds the Pacu extremely delicious.

Name: Pacu
Description:
Pacus are aquatic creatures that can live in any liquid, such as Water or Contaminated Water.

Every organism in the known universe finds the Pacu extremely delicious.
